Poland cuts min price of 1 - yr index - linked bond . Poland cut the minimum price of one - year index linked bonds to 95 . 00 from 96 . 65 at the last auction on August 27 , the treasury said . It said the average price was 95 . 99 , down from 96 . 75 . The treasury sold six million zlotys of the bonds , whose base interest rate is the cumulated inflation rate of 12 months , after institutional investors bid for 68 . 5 million at the 200 million zloty tender . The value date for this auction is November 5 , 1996 and the bonds mature on December 3 , 1997 . - - Warsaw Newsroom + 48 22 653 9700 
